<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 93 / Finance and the Family: Schroders share service - At a
Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Schroders has launched a dealing service for those who want to buy and sell
shares in its split fund, and might not have their own stockbroker. Dealing
charges are 1 per cent on both purchases and sales. There is a daily dealing
facility for those who invest the minimum of Pounds 1,000. The split fund
was launched in March and has income, zero and capital shares.
