<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 93 / Finance and the Family: Going Dutch on shares - At a Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Robeco, the Dutch investment company, is celebrating its 60th anniversary
and is offering investors the chance to buy shares free of commission and
brokerage charges through its Swiss bank subsidiary. The minimum investment
is for Pounds 5,000, or Dollars 10,000, and involves opening an account at
the bank; the offer lasts until June 30. Robeco is an open-ended investment
company which owns shares in around 400 companies in 20 countries.
