<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Chiltern Radio deficit widens
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Losses at Chiltern Radio rose from Pounds 179,000 to Pounds 325,000 pre-tax
for the six months ended March 31. For the full year to end-September 1992
the group incurred a deficit of Pounds 392,000.
The first half loss took account of an exceptional provision of Pounds
77,000 in respect of a permanent diminution in value of the company's
investment in Independent Radio News.
Turnover of Pounds 2.75m compared with Pounds 2.55m. Losses per share
emerged at 3.4p (1.9p).
</TEXT>
