<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 93 / Court move on Sunday shopping
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE High Court has ruled that the judicial review sought by retailers Tesco
Stores and Texas Homecare, which claim they have been unfairly discriminated
against by councils enforcing laws banning Sunday trading, should be speeded
up. The review is likely to be heard next month.
The retailers are seeking a review on the grounds that they have been
unlawfully targeted and threatened with trading bans, while smaller
businesses are escaping legal action.
Mr Peter Lloyd, a Home Office minister, told the Commons yesterday that the
government would publish a bill in the next few weeks aimed at sorting out
the Sunday trading muddle.
