<HEADLINE>
FT  14 MAY 93 / Helsinki defiant on pay bill
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HELSINKI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
FINLAND'S government is to present a bill allowing employers to pay 30 per
cent below minimum wage if they hire jobless youths, AP reports from
Helsinki.
'We are not engaging in slave labour; we are simply giving work to the
young,' said Mr Esko Aho, prime minister. Unions have threatened strikes if
the bill goes ahead.
Unemployment is at a post-war record rate of 17.8 per cent.
