<HEADLINE>
FT  14 MAY 93 / London Stock Exchange: Zeneca shunned
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, PETER JOHN and JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Investors continued to shun Zeneca, the bioscience side of the soon to be
demerged ICI. However, at least one leading securities house was arguing
that Zeneca offered good value.
Agency broker James Capel believes that the ICI new shares have been
overvalued and, although there are some long-term worries with Zeneca, it
may not be receiving the sector rating it deserves. Williams de Broe has
also told clients it believes the Zeneca price is too low. Nevertheless, the
majority view held sway yesterday and ICI new gained 14 at 623p while Zeneca
ex-rights lost 16 to 648p and the nil-paid shed 13 1/2 to 52 1/2 p. Existing
ICI fell 5 1/2 to 1279p.
