FT  14 MAY 93 / International Company News: Sale of German mines finalised
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Treuhand, the agency responsible for privatising eastern German
industry, yesterday concluded the sale of the region's potash mines in a
contract giving it a 49 per cent stake in the new company, write Judy
Dempsey and David Waller. The contract will involve the Treuhand in a DM1bn
